PART 5: INTEGRATION WITH YOUR EXISTING SYSTEM
================================================================================

5.1 WHERE DEFI FITS YOUR PHASES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Phase 3 (Months 7-12): FOUNDATION ONLY
• NO DeFi activities
• Focus on simple engines (DCA, ETFs, Gold, LISA)
• Build understanding of crypto basics first

Phase 4 (Year 2): INTRODUCTION
• Simple lending (Aave, Compound)
• Single-asset staking (Ethereum 2.0 if available)
• Low complexity, trackable activities
• Maximum £50-100 allocated

Phase 5 (Year 3+): EXPANSION
• Liquidity provision (if experienced)
• Yield farming (if willing to track extensively)
• Flash loans (only with full understanding)
• Maximum 5% of total portfolio

5.2 SPREADSHEET INTEGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

New Sheet: DeFi_Tracker in PERSONAL_PROFILE_SYSTEM.xlsx

Columns:
- Date | Protocol | Activity | Asset Deposited | Amount | GBP Value | Asset Received | Amount | GBP Value | Income Taxable | CGT Taxable | Cumulative Income | Notes

Formula Integration:
• Sum all Income Taxable = Annual DeFi Income
• Feed to tax calculation sheet
• Track against £1,000 Trading Allowance
• Auto-calculate cumulative position

5.3 KOINLY INTEGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

For DeFi tracking:
• Upgrade to Koinly paid plan (£49-99/year)
• Connect all wallets used for DeFi
• Import CSV for unsupported protocols
• Review classifications (Income vs CGT)
• Generate DeFi-specific report

Monthly Action:
• Export Koinly report
• Review DeFi transactions
• Check income calculations
• Reconcile with your spreadsheet

5.4 TAX SINKING FUND ADJUSTMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Current Tax Sinking Fund: £20/month (for CGT on crypto sales)

With DeFi Income Tax liability:
• Increase to £30-40/month
• Separate sub-pot for DeFi Income Tax
• Track expected liability quarterly

Formula:
Expected DeFi Income Tax = (Estimated Annual DeFi Income) × Tax Rate

Example:
• Expected DeFi income: £500/year
• Tax rate: 20%
• Expected tax: £100
• Monthly sinking fund: £8.33

5.5 BUSINESS VS PERSONAL DEFI
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If operating DeFi through business:
• All income = Trading income
• Expenses deductible (gas fees, software)
• Corporation Tax if Ltd company (25%)
• Income Tax if sole trader (20-45%)

Personal DeFi:
• Trading Allowance may apply
• Simpler structure
• Cannot deduct expenses (unless trading classification)

Recommendation: Keep DeFi personal until Year 3+

================================================================================
PART 6: RISK WARNINGS AND BEST PRACTICES
================================================================================

6.1 SMART CONTRACT RISKS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DeFi Risk Factors:
• Smart contract bugs/hacks
• Protocol insolvency
• Impermanent loss (LP providers)
• Governance attacks
• Oracle failures
• Flash loan attacks on protocols

Tax Implication of Losses:
• Hacked/stolen crypto: MAY claim capital loss
• Evidence required (police report, protocol announcement)
• HMRC discretion
• Not guaranteed

Best Practice:
• Only use audited protocols (Certik, Trail of Bits)
• Diversify across protocols
• Never more than 5% in DeFi
• Insurance where available (Nexus Mutual)

6.2 REGULATORY RISKS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Future HMRC Changes:
• DeFi taxation evolving
• New guidance expected
• Potential alignment with traditional finance
• Some protocols may be prohibited

Stay Informed:
• Check HMRC Cryptoassets Manual quarterly
• Follow crypto tax specialists on Twitter/X
• Join UK crypto tax communities
• Consider accountant consultation (Year 2+)

6.3 RECORD KEEPING BEST PRACTICES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Daily:
• Screenshot major transactions
• Note transaction hashes
• Record gas fees

Weekly:
• Export wallet transaction history
• Reconcile with protocol interfaces
• Note any airdrops or rewards

Monthly:
• Import to Koinly
• Review classifications
• Update spreadsheet
• Calculate running tax estimate

Annually:
• Generate full tax report
• File Self Assessment
• Pay tax due
• Archive records

6.4 WHEN TO CONSULT AN ACCOUNTANT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Consult professional if:
• DeFi income exceeds £5,000/year
• Complex multi-protocol strategies
• Uncertain about trading vs investing classification
• Business involvement
• HMRC inquiry received
• Significant gains/losses to report

Cost: £200-500 for consultation
Benefit: Correct tax treatment, peace of mind

