PART 7: DEFI STRATEGY FOR YOUR SITUATION
================================================================================

7.1 RECOMMENDED DEFI JOURNEY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

YEAR 1 (Current): NO DEFI
• Focus on Phase 1-3 foundations
• Learn about DeFi conceptually
• Track developments
• Build capital base first

YEAR 2: SIMPLE LENDING
• Month 13-18: Aave or Compound
• Single asset deposit (ETH or stablecoin)
• £50-100 allocation maximum
• Focus on learning, not returns
• Track every transaction

YEAR 2 (Late): ETH STAKING
• If Ethereum withdrawal available
• Consider Lido or Rocket Pool
• £100-200 allocation
• Long-term hold (5+ years)

YEAR 3+: EXPANDED DEFI
• Liquidity provision (if confident)
• Yield farming (if willing to track)
• Maximum 5% of total portfolio
• Only with full tracking capability

7.2 DEFI PLATFORMS RECOMMENDED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

BEGINNER-FRIENDLY (Year 2):
• Aave (lending, established)
• Compound (lending, simple)
• Lido (ETH staking, liquid)

INTERMEDIATE (Year 3):
• Uniswap v3 (concentrated liquidity)
• Curve (stablecoin LP)
• Rocket Pool (decentralized staking)

ADVANCED (Year 3+):
• Convex (yield optimization)
• Yearn (vault strategies)
• Various Layer 2 protocols

7.3 TAX-EFFICIENT DEFI STRATEGIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Strategy 1: Utilize Trading Allowance
• Keep DeFi income under £1,000/year initially
• No tax, no reporting complexity
• Build experience without tax burden

Strategy 2: Time Reward Claims
• If possible, claim rewards in low-income years
• Basic rate taxpayer vs higher rate = significant difference
• Example: £1,000 income at 20% = £200 tax, at 40% = £400 tax

Strategy 3: Offset Gains with Losses
• If DeFi generates capital losses (impermanent loss)
• Offset against crypto trading gains
• Reduce overall CGT liability

Strategy 4: ISA for DeFi Exposure (Limited)
• Some DeFi exposure through crypto ETPs in ISA
• Not direct DeFi but correlated exposure
• Tax-free wrapper

